id: pm-mfkv92
title: "GH-623: opt-in post-merge history reconciliation hook and one-command verify repair"
description: GitHub issue #623 reports that a successful git merge can leave history verification red until a separate manual history-repair pass; provide an explicit safe reconciliation workflow without weakening verification.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[5]: agent-ux,"area:history","area:merge",gh-issue,multi-agent
created_at: "2026-07-20T09:12:15.195Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T09:15:21.822Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T09:15:21.026Z"
author: codex-20260720
acceptance_criteria: "An opt-in post-merge hook or one-command reconcile path detects merged history drift, previews the affected streams, performs audited field-aware repair, and leaves pm history --verify plus pm validate green; default git hooks remain non-surprising; docs and sandboxed merge acceptance tests cover enable, skip, failure, and recovery paths."
parent: pm-o2kc
resolution: Added public runMergeReconcile SDK orchestration and pm merge reconcile preview/apply workflow with post-repair validation.
expected_result: Operators can preview or repair merged history drift in one audited command without installing surprising automatic hooks.
actual_result: "Preview, apply, clean no-op, usage failure, stale-lock failure, merge safety, and installed-package reconciliation all pass."
