comments[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-20T09:12:15.195Z",codex-20260720,"Duplicate check 2026-07-20: pm search across all statuses for GH-623 and merge history verify red/manual history-repair found no live item; closed pm-g5sx and pm-wc1r provide the shipped merge-driver lineage, while this item captures the newly reported opt-in post-merge orchestration gap. Source: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/623"
  "2026-07-21T07:33:04.020Z",codex-root-20260721,"Evidence: pm merge reconcile now previews or applies bulk audited repair followed by history-drift and storage-integrity validation. Acceptance covers drift preview, successful repair, clean no-op, invalid positional input, stale-lock repair failure, and an installed-package reconciliation."
  "2026-07-21T07:54:39.838Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final verification: direct SDK, Commander registration, and command-level reconcile suites pass; the repo-wide coverage gate now reports exactly 100% lines/statements/functions/branches (39551/39551, 40658/40658, 8259/8259, 28612/28612)."
  "2026-07-21T08:12:06.896Z",codex-root-20260721,"Greptile remediation: clarified the public MergeReconcileResult.ok contract—dry-run success means the preview completed without errors, not that validation is green; SDK callers must inspect repair and validation checks before applying."
  "2026-07-21T08:16:40.942Z",codex-root-20260721,"Final review-head proof: clarified dry-run semantics pass docstring, focused, and full-suite gates; 6052 tests pass at exact 100% coverage."
  "2026-07-21T09:10:31.676Z",codex-root-20260721,"Hosted review remediation: failed apply-mode reconciliation now returns explicit incomplete/do-not-commit guidance rather than success guidance. Direct SDK coverage asserts the failure contract."
  "2026-07-21T09:15:17.459Z",codex-root-20260721,"Exact remediation-head proof: all 332 test files and 6053 tests pass at 100/100/100/100 coverage, including explicit failed-apply guidance and the command/SDK reconciliation contracts."
